-- Mexico to Swap Fixed-Rate Peso Bonds on Aug. 1
-- B y   B e n   B a i n
-- 2012-07-30T17:25:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-30/mexico-to-swap-fixed-rate-peso-bonds-on-aug-1-correct-.html
(Corrects amount of bonds to be exchanged and maturity.)  Mexico  will swap out as much as 22
billion pesos of fixed-rate bonds.  The nation’s central bank will oversee an auction for the
 Finance Ministry  on Aug. 1 of bonds maturing in 2016, 2017, 2018
and 2024. The securities will be exchanged for debt maturing in
2014, 2015, 2016, 2021 and 2027, according to a statement posted
today on the central bank’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Bain in Mexico City at 
 bbain2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Roeder at 
 jroeder@bloomberg.net  